ğŸ“– English Grammar Guide

Sample grammar topics with English & Urdu explanations

1. Present Simple Tense

English: Used for habits, routines, and general truths.

Urdu: Aadat, routine, aur aam sach ke liye istemal hota hai.

Structure: Subject + Verb (base form)

â€¢ I work every day. (Main roz kaam karta hoon)

â€¢ She works at a bank. (Woh bank mein kaam karti hai)

2. Past Simple Tense

English: Used for completed actions in the past.

Urdu: Mazee mein mukammal honay wale kaam ke liye.

Structure: Subject + Verb-ed / Irregular verb

â€¢ I worked yesterday. (Main kal kaam kiya)

â€¢ He went to school. (Woh school gaya)

3. Articles (a, an, the)

English: 'A/an' for non-specific items, 'the' for specific items.

Urdu: 'A/an' aam cheez ke liye, 'the' khaas cheez ke liye.

â€¢ I saw a cat. (Main ne ek billi dekhi)

â€¢ The cat was black. (Woh billi kaali thi)

4. Pronouns (I, you, he, she, it, we, they)

English: Words used instead of nouns.

Urdu: Zameer - naam ki jagah istemal hote hain.

â€¢ I am a student. (Main student hoon)

â€¢ He is my friend. (Woh mera dost hai)

â€¢ They are happy. (Woh khush hain)

5. Question Formation

English: Start with question words or auxiliary verbs.

Urdu: Sawal banaanay ke liye helping verbs ya sawal ke lafz se shuru karein.

â€¢ What is your name? (Tumhara naam kya hai?)

â€¢ Do you like tea? (Kya tumhe chai pasand hai?)

â€¢ Where are you going? (Tum kahan ja rahay ho?)

Note: Full version will include 30 grammar topics covering A1 to C1 levels!
